n. It’s important to ensure that everything’s managed correctly so I don’t accidentally delete the wrong files. Let's keep it tidy!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Figuring out file handling**\\n\\nI need to consider using a native image with temporary file templates that are discovered after the image build. This involves dynamic code loading, and I should catch existing handles if they're unsupported. If I'm running under the JVM, there shouldn’t be an issue, but I also need to account for external files. It's crucial to ensure that cleanup deletes files, even if they weren't created, using Files.deleteIfExists. I'll need to evaluate if URLClassLoader should be imported, but maybe not. Time to edit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_r6haLiCfzKMQZIf8xQDccF3n|fc_0e6d05979465efaa016a0010615324819182e94607067e5cdd", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-templates/4.0.24/src/test/groovy/org_apache_groovy/groovy_templates/Groovy_templatesTest.groovy", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void markupTemplateEngineBuildsEscapedMarkupWithConfiguration() {\n        String rendered = executeTemplateOperation {\n            TemplateConfiguration configuration = new TemplateConfiguration()\n            configuration.setAutoEscape(true)\n            configuration.setAutoIndent(true)\n            configuration.setAutoNewLine(true)\n            configuration.setUseDoubleQuotes(true)\n\n            MarkupTemplateEngine engine = new MarkupTemplateEngine(configuration)\n            Template template = engine.createTemplate('''yieldUnescaped '<!DOCTYPE html>'\nhtml {\n    head {\n        title(pageTitle)\n    }\n    body {\n        h1(\"Welcome $user\")\n        ul {\n            items.each { item ->\n                li(item)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n''')\n            template.make([\n                    pageTitle: 'Shopping & tasks',\n                    user     : '<Ada>',\n                    items    : ['tea', 'ca